<item>
            <title>[FLINK-26853] HeapStateBackend ignores metadata updates in certain cases</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-26853</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On recovery, HeapRestoreOperation reads state handles one by one;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;each handle contains metadata at the beginning;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the metadata is always read, but not actually used if a state with the corresponding name was already registered&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In a rare case of downscaling + multiple checkpoints with different metadata; this might lead to data being deserialized incorrectly (always using the initial metadata).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It also prevents incremental checkpoints with schema evolution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On first access, however, the backend itself will update (merge) metadata; so that it doesn&apos;t affect new state updates.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
